Based on beads dependencies.go, adapted for Phase 1 (in-memory + petgraph):

**Dependency Types**:
1. blocks: Hard blocker (prevents work)
2. related: Soft link (informational)
3. parent-child: Hierarchical (epics→tasks)
4. discovered-from: Found during work

**Phase 1 Implementation (In-Memory + petgraph)**:
```rust
impl InMemoryStorage {
    fn add_dependency(
        &mut self, 
        from: &IssueId, 
        to: &IssueId, 
        dep_type: DependencyType
    ) -> Result<()> {
        // Cycle detection using petgraph
        if self.has_cycle(from, to)? {
            return Err(Error::CircularDependency);
        }

        // Add edge to graph
        let from_node = self.node_map.get(from)?;
        let to_node = self.node_map.get(to)?;
        self.graph.add_edge(*from_node, *to_node, dep_type);

        // Update issue's dependency list
        let issue = self.issues.get_mut(from)?;
        issue.dependencies.push(Dependency { 
            depends_on_id: to.clone(), 
            dep_type 
        });

        Ok(())
    }

    fn has_cycle(&self, from: &IssueId, to: &IssueId) -> Result<bool> {
        use petgraph::algo;
        let from_node = self.node_map.get(from)?;
        let to_node = self.node_map.get(to)?;

        // Check if adding edge creates cycle
        Ok(algo::has_path_connecting(&self.graph, *to_node, *from_node, None))
    }
}
```

**Phase 3 (PostgreSQL)**: Will use recursive CTEs for cycle detection:
```sql
WITH RECURSIVE paths AS (
    SELECT issue_id, depends_on_id, 1 as depth
    FROM dependencies WHERE issue_id = ?
    UNION ALL
    SELECT d.issue_id, d.depends_on_id, p.depth + 1
    FROM dependencies d JOIN paths p 
    ON d.issue_id = p.depends_on_id
    WHERE p.depth < 100
)
SELECT EXISTS(SELECT 1 FROM paths WHERE depends_on_id = ?)
```

```rust
impl<T> JsonlQuery<T>
where
    T: DeserializeOwned + 'static,
{
    pub fn execute<R>(
        self,
        reader: R
    ) -> impl Stream<Item = Result<T>>
    where
        R: AsyncRead + Unpin,
    {
        let jsonl_reader = JsonlReader::new(reader);
        let stream = jsonl_reader.stream::<T>();

        stream.filter_map(move |result| {
            let matches = match &result {
                Ok(value) => self.matches(value),
                Err(_) => true, // Pass errors through
            };

            async move {
                if matches {
                    Some(result)
                } else {
                    None
                }
            }
        })
    }
}
```

```rust
use serde::Serialize;
use tokio::io::AsyncWriteExt;

impl<W: AsyncWrite + Unpin> JsonlWriter<W> {
    pub async fn write<T: Serialize>(&mut self, value: &T) -> Result<()> {
        let json = serde_json::to_string(value)?;
        self.writer.write_all(json.as_bytes()).await?;
        self.writer.write_all(b"\n").await?;
        Ok(())
    }

    pub async fn write_all<T: Serialize>(
        &mut self,
        values: impl IntoIterator<Item = T>,
    ) -> Result<()> {
        for value in values {
            self.write(&value).await?;
        }
        Ok(())
    }

    pub async fn flush(&mut self) -> Result<()> {
        self.writer.flush().await?;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

